# {{project_name}}

## Repo rules (enforced by reassure)

This repo uses [operation-reassurance](https://github.com/avarga1/operation-reassurance)
to enforce structural rules via the MCP server.

### Before writing any file

**Call `check_repo_rules` before every Write or Edit.**

Pass the absolute file path and the full proposed content.
- `severity: error` — fix the violation before proceeding. Do not write the file.
- `severity: warning` — flag it in your response. Fix before merging.

This is not optional. Skipping this check will introduce violations that block CI.

### Before creating a new file

**Call `check_repo_rules` with the proposed path and content first.**
If the file is in `lib/` and is a `.dart` file, the flutter preset applies.

### Key rules for this stack

| Rule | Severity | What it catches | Use instead |
|------|----------|-----------------|-------------|
| no-print-in-prod | error | `print()` in lib/ | `logger.d()` |
| no-inline-mock-data | error | MockData/FakeData/testUser in prod | test fixtures only |
| no-hardcoded-urls | error | Inline http/https strings | env config |
| no-localhost | error | localhost/127.0.0.1 in prod | env config |
| no-hardcoded-colors | warning | `Colors.red`, `Color(0x…)` | `context.colorScheme.*` |
| no-inline-text-style | warning | `TextStyle(fontSize:…)` | `context.textTheme.*` |
| no-imperative-navigation | warning | `Navigator.push` | `context.router.push(…)` |
| no-media-query-size | warning | `MediaQuery.of(context).size` | `MediaQuery.sizeOf(context)` |
| no-raw-border-radius | warning | `BorderRadius.circular(…)` | `AppRadii.mdAll` |
| no-raw-edge-insets | warning | `EdgeInsets.symmetric(…)` | `AppSpacing.mdAll` |
| no-raw-sized-box-spacing | warning | `SizedBox(height:…)` | `AppSpacing.hMd` |
| no-theme-of-context | warning | `Theme.of(context)` | `context.colorScheme` |
| no-raw-duration | warning | `Duration(milliseconds:…)` | `AppDurations.medium2` |

### MCP tools available

- `check_repo_rules(path, proposed_content)` — check before every write
- `list_repo_rule_presets()` — see all available rulesets
- `get_symbol_map(path)` — understand what already exists before adding new code
- `get_uncovered_symbols(path)` — find untested public API
- `get_dark_modules(path)` — find unobserved production code

Run `reassure .` locally for a full repo health report.
